<section class="container mb-12">
    <h2>
        How it all started:
    </h2>
    <ul>
        <li>
            My first contact with a computer was at 11 years old.
        </li>
        <li>
            The first thing I learned to do on one was play Age of Empires II.
        </li>
        <li>
            In 2004, I moved to the city, and that same year we got our first computer at home.
        </li>
        <li>
            That same year, I took a computer apart for the first time without knowing how to put it back together. Everything turned out fine! :)
        </li>
        <li>
            I learned how a computer works and how to assemble and disassemble one.
        </li>
        <li>
            I learned how to install Windows XP and format a machine.
        </li>
        <li>
            I started repairing the computers of my friends and neighbors.
        </li>
        <li>
            During the hype of hi5.com, I learned HTML and CSS to customize my profile and my friends' profiles — my first real encounter with web development.
        </li>
        <li>
            In 2010, I discovered Linux and fell in love with Ubuntu.
        </li>
        <li>
            In 2011, I started a YouTube channel to share what I knew about Ubuntu and Linux. I eventually stopped making videos. :(
        </li>
        <li>
            In 2012, with the rise of smartphones, I got into Android and started contributing to the XDA Developers community.
        </li>
        <li>
            In 2012, I earned a higher diploma in Graphic Design.
        </li>
        <li>
            In 2013, I started a Bachelor's in Infotechnology Engineering at José Cecilio del Valle University.
        </li>
    </ul>
</section>